vocabinfos.mediumDef:
A man descended from Senaah (H5570) of the tribe of Levi before time of Exile and Return, only mentioned at 1Ch.9.7; including Hodaviah (H1938I) and Judah (H3063I); also called Hassenaah at Neh.3.3
Another name of se.nu.ah (סְנוּאָה "Hassenuah" H5574)
§ Senaah or Hassenaah [with the article] = "thorny"
ancestor of a family who returned from exile with Zerubbabel
